Author: fazer#0903
Content:
Hellow, yesterday i was testing atomic-dex password leak as plaintext into "user custom learned words db" on multiple phones and android versions like android 5, 6... and all leaking.
By analysis, input fields ARE NOT protected when user clicks on unhide button before clicks on input field.
If user password is like "LetterLetterLetterNumSpecialSymbol" only special-symbol from pass is not stored in. But if hacker uses dictionary attack, pass can be broken by few minutes.
